  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CIR - Land and Sustainable Development of Indigenous Peoples in Roraima</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to guarantee the collective rights and autonomy of indigenous people from 33 indigenous territories so they can live sustainably in Roraima, North Brazil.

Many indigenous territories in Roraima have been demarcated, but many challenges still remain to ensure that indigenous communities in this region are able to live sustainably. These include: lack of food security, adequate public policy implementation in indigenous lands (e.g. health and education), and land invasions (e.g. large-scale projects such as hydro-electric dams and mining).

The Indigenous Council of Roraima (CIR) is a representative indigenous grassroots organisation, and will undertake the following activities: community mobilisation, advocacy, lobbying, communications and awareness raising activities, and judicial accompaniment in the areas of health, education, cultural preservation, environmental and land management. CAFOD&apos;s support is focused on two key results: 

1. Protection and conservation of natural resources is improved in indigenous territories, and the impacts of climate change are mitigated by communities. 
2. CIR as an institution is strengthened via improved political and financial sustainability and project management.</narrative>
  </description>
